{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2bf775f1-eb31-4c04-9ca9-cfa39a92d154","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, and the reason string appears in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3a20296f-7bb1-45c5-8ee0-f6589304d1dd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without tools.","outputTokens":309,"requestId":"0BC1:1D28CE:574927:658FB7:69F009B7"},"id":"f27ae1ec-23d0-4f0f-bf61-af3db006842b","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:13:34.578Z","parentId":"bc98b5b8-73bd-459d-9234-867b56c2953c"}
